  "school": "ICT",
  "asset": "TSLA",
  "timeframe": "1D",
  "market_context": "Monday–Wednesday showed higher expansion in TSLA; Thursday countered the range without taking out Wednesday’s high. Intermarket analysis revealed NQ reversed on Wednesday, suggesting Thursday was a continuation of that midweek reversal, setting up Friday’s move toward weekly open and low.",
  "key_observation": "Thursday did not break Wednesday’s high but still countered the weekly range, and NQ’s Wednesday reversal provided intermarket confirmation for a bearish bias into Friday.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified Monday–Wednesday as an expansion higher phase in TSLA’s weekly profile.",
    "Step 2: Noted Thursday failed to take out Wednesday’s high but still countered the range, qualifying it as a 'Thursday Counter' despite imperfection.",
    "Step 3: Applied intermarket analysis to NQ (15-min), observing a reversal formed on Wednesday—indicating Thursday was a continuation of that midweek reversal.",
    "Step 4: Concluded Friday’s bias was bearish toward the weekly open and current week’s low, which price subsequently achieved."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Even imperfect weekly profiles (e.g., no high break) can be traded when supported by intermarket SMT divergences; midweek reversals in correlated assets like NQ enhance confidence in Thursday counter setups.",
